casebody.data:
March 12, 1951. No. 294,

Misc.

Moore, doing business as Moore’s Bakery, v. Mead Service Co. et al. Per Curiam:

The petition for writ *945of certiorari is granted. The judgment of the Court of Appeals is vacated and the case is remanded to that court for further consideration in the light of Kiefer-Stewart Co. v. Joseph E. Seagram & Sons, ante, p. 211.

Dee C. Blythe for petitioner. Edward W. Napier, Howard F. Houk and Leslie Humphrey for respondents.
